## Read these skills first — they are binding

The engineering standards for this repo are encoded as skills under
`.claude/skills/`. **Adopt them on every change:**

1. **[`property-based-testing`](.claude/skills/property-based-testing/SKILL.md)** —
   every new pure function ships with at least one **Hypothesis** property test
   (idempotency, invariants, round-trip, metamorphic). A shrinking counterexample
   is a real bug.
2. **[`python-clean-code`](.claude/skills/python-clean-code/SKILL.md)** — small,
   single-responsibility, **fully-typed** functions with docstrings; guard clauses;
   no dead code. Must pass `ruff`, `black`, and `mypy` clean.
3. **[`git-ci-governance`](.claude/skills/git-ci-governance/SKILL.md)** —
   `main`/`dev`/`staging`; branches named **exactly** `feature/<ticket>-<slug>`,
   `bug/<ticket>-<slug>`, or `hotfix/<ticket>-<slug>`; Conventional Commits; PRs
   into `dev` with review + CODEOWNERS + green Build/Test/Validate; CI references
   the **reusable workflows** only — never inline pipeline logic.

## Project layout

```
src/{{ package_name }}/   # pure, typed domain logic in core.py{% if service_kind == 'rest-api' %} + api.py (FastAPI){% endif %}

tests/                    # test_smoke.py + test_properties.py (Hypothesis)
docs/                     # MkDocs site (build with --strict)
.github/workflows/        # build/test/validate → reusable platform workflows
```

## Local commands

```bash
pip install -e ".[dev]"{% if service_kind == 'rest-api' %} && pip install -e ".[api]"{% endif %}

pytest                # smoke + property tests
ruff check .          # lint
black --check .       # format check
mypy                  # types
mkdocs build --strict # docs
```

## Non-negotiables (summary)

- New pure function ⇒ at least one property test.
- Keep functions small, typed, documented; keep the tool gate green.
- Respect the branch model and naming; PRs go into `dev`.
- CI uses the reusable workflows — do not copy pipeline logic into this repo.

When in doubt, open the relevant `SKILL.md` and follow it.
